01:03:15,900 --> 01:03:17,300
Okay.

795
01:03:19,200 --> 01:03:20,500
Come on.

796
01:03:26,100 --> 01:03:28,000
Here, take a seat.

797
01:03:28,300 --> 01:03:29,900
MELANIE:
Okay.

798
01:03:32,400 --> 01:03:35,300
I'm gonna take your hands for a second,
to get a connection...

799
01:03:35,500 --> 01:03:38,700
...and then I'll let go, and I'll just
ask you a couple questions.

800
01:03:38,900 --> 01:03:40,000
All right.

801
01:03:40,200 --> 01:03:41,500
Okay. Give me your hands.

802
01:03:42,500 --> 01:03:43,900
Okay.

803
01:03:46,000 --> 01:03:47,200
[WHOOSH]

804
01:03:51,300 --> 01:03:52,600
Okay.

805
01:03:55,400 --> 01:03:59,100
There's a woman. And she's tall.

806
01:03:59,600 --> 01:04:02,600
Thin. She has brown hair.

807
01:04:04,300 --> 01:04:06,500
Do you know who I'm talking about?

808
01:04:09,700 --> 01:04:11,100
Is this woman your mother?

809
01:04:13,200 --> 01:04:14,800
Yes.

810
01:04:16,300 --> 01:04:18,500
And I'm feeling a pain in my chest.

811
01:04:22,100 --> 01:04:27,200
Yeah. That's how she died.
Of a heart attack.

812
01:04:27,400 --> 01:04:28,700
I'm sorry.

813
01:04:32,200 --> 01:04:33,700
Okay. You ready to eat?

814
01:04:37,600 --> 01:04:39,700
There's not something else?

815
01:04:39,800 --> 01:04:43,200
- No, there's nothing...
- No, no, no, I can tell.

816
01:04:43,400 --> 01:04:46,200
Please, there is, I can tell.

817
01:04:47,300 --> 01:04:51,400
I mean, what's the matter?
You don't think I could handle it?

818
01:04:54,900 --> 01:04:57,100
All right, um...

819
01:04:59,200 --> 01:05:01,600
When you touched me before,
there was a...

820
01:05:02,200 --> 01:05:04,000
There was a man.

821
01:05:05,400 --> 01:05:06,700
Dark hair.

822
01:05:12,500 --> 01:05:14,200
My father.

823
01:05:14,400 --> 01:05:16,100
He passed away not too long ago?

824
01:05:17,300 --> 01:05:19,700
- Last year.
- And...

825
01:05:21,000 --> 01:05:24,400
All he kept saying,
all I kept hearing was...

826
01:05:24,600 --> 01:05:25,700
Was what?

827
01:05:29,400 --> 01:05:30,800
How sorry he was.

828
01:05:33,300 --> 01:05:34,700
What for?

829
01:05:34,900 --> 01:05:38,600
For what he did to you all that time ago.

830
01:05:42,100 --> 01:05:48,100
And he hoped
that you could one day forgive him.

831
01:05:51,800 --> 01:05:53,100
I'm sorry.

832
01:05:58,400 --> 01:06:00,100
I'm sorry.

833
01:06:02,000 --> 01:06:04,300
I'm sorry...

834
01:06:07,500 --> 01:06:09,800
...for pressing you like that.

835
01:06:13,400 --> 01:06:17,800
Maybe we shouldn't have gone there.

836
01:06:20,200 --> 01:06:22,200
I don't know what to say.

837
01:06:28,400 --> 01:06:30,500
Except if I...

838
01:06:30,700 --> 01:06:34,100
If I go now...

839
01:06:35,200 --> 01:06:38,800
...if we draw a line under this...

840
01:06:39,200 --> 01:06:41,700
...pretend it never happened...

841
01:06:47,800 --> 01:06:49,500
...we'll be okay.

842
01:06:50,800 --> 01:06:52,100
I'm sure.

843
01:06:53,000 --> 01:06:54,300
Good.

844
01:06:56,300 --> 01:06:57,800
Good.

845
01:07:08,800 --> 01:07:12,400
We still have the competition
to win. Right?

846
01:07:12,800 --> 01:07:14,200
Right.

847
01:07:16,000 --> 01:07:18,500
I should've listened to you.

848
01:07:18,700 --> 01:07:22,000
You know, too much knowledge
and all that.

849
01:07:31,600 --> 01:07:33,300
I'll see you next week.

850
01:07:33,500 --> 01:07:35,000
Yeah, you betcha.

